      "rationale": "NIH predictions compared against three independent experimental datasets using validation metrics: E_rel = 18.4% (95% CI 9.1%–27.7%). Although confidence score is explicitly rated 0.61 (moderate-low) due to donor blood rheology variability, the metric remains within the pre-specified 30% acceptance threshold for Gradation 2 at MRL 2. Wide uncertainty bounds are honestly documented and accepted as residual risk.",
